	   <tr><td colspan=2>Certainly, keep BS and pierce maxed at all times, which will occur naturally in group combat.&nbsp;&nbsp;At level 21 I decided to work on 1hs, in case I picked up a good stat weapon.  I bought a cheap whip from a ranger.  It is something like 3/17 but dont quote me.  I use it in my off hand just to raise the 1hs.  It only hits for 2 or 3 points but raises 1hs and dual wield very quickly.  Main damage is going to be BS anyway, right?!  I keep the SBD handy to swap in areas where every hp matters, or if I have to solo something.  At level 28 i just saw my 1hs hit 101, and it is coming all the time, painlessly.  I may never use the 1hs, but it seems like a good skill.  I wish I could find a way to raise hand to hand easily, for body runs, etc. but cant figure a quick and easy way for that.  God speed my friend.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
